{A new series of tournaments was started, before the events in Palma de
Mallorca finished. The publisher Jorge Puig Laborda became the director of the
new tournaments in Las Palmas. The event was called 'Gran torneo internacional
de ajedrez Ciudad Las Palmas Gran Canaria'. Sponsor money came from the
tourist industry. Sixteen players competed in the great Hotel Santa Catalina
from 29 v until 17 vi 1972, before the match Spassky - Fisher began.} 1. e4 c5
2. c3 Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. d4 cxd4 5. cxd4 d6 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. Nc3 dxe5 8. dxe5 Ndb4
$5 ({The alternative is} 8... Nxc3 9. Qxd8+ Kxd8 10. bxc3 Bg4) 9. a3 Qxd1+ 10.
Kxd1 Na6 11. b4 Nc7 12. h3 $6 Be6 13. Bd3 g6 14. Bb2 Bg7 15. Ne4 Bd5 16. b5 $2
(16. Ke2 $1 {leads to an edge for Black.}) 16... Nxb5 $1 17. Nf6+ $5 Bxf6 $1 {
He gains material.} (17... exf6 $2 18. exf6 O-O 19. fxg7 Rfd8 20. Ke2 {
brings counter-play for White.}) 18. exf6 Bxf3+ 19. gxf3 O-O-O $1 20. fxe7
Rxd3+ 21. Ke2 Rd4 $1 22. a4 Nd6 23. Rac1 Nf5 24. Rhd1 Kd7 25. Rxc6 Kxc6 26.
Bxd4 Nxd4+ 27. Rxd4 Re8 {Black has achieved a won rook endgame.} 28. Re4 Kd6
29. Kd3 Rxe7 30. Rh4 h5 31. Rd4+ Kc6 32. Rc4+ Kb6 33. f4 f5 34. Rd4 Ka5 35. Rd6
Rg7 36. Rd4 Rc7 37. Kd2 Rc6 38. h4 Re6 39. Rd7 Rb6 {
Black will win another pawn.} 0-1

